a. To create a contact form using HTML
b. To include input fields, text areas, and buttons for user interaction
c. To understand the structure and functionality of HTML forms for data collection

Hereâ€™s the HTML code that matches your experiment perfectly ðŸ‘‡

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Contact Form</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Contact Us</h1>

    <form action="#" method="post">
        <!-- Name -->
        <label for="name"><b>Full Name:</b></label><br>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" placeholder="Enter your name" required><br><br>

        <!-- Email -->
        <label for="email"><b>Email Address:</b></label><br>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="Enter your email" required><br><br>

        <!-- Phone -->
        <label for="phone"><b>Phone Number:</b></label><br>
        <input type="tel" id="phone" name="phone" placeholder="Enter your phone number"><br><br>

        <!-- Subject -->
        <label for="subject"><b>Subject:</b></label><br>
        <input type="text" id="subject" name="subject" placeholder="Enter subject"><br><br>

        <!-- Message -->
        <label for="message"><b>Message:</b></label><br>
        <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" cols="30" placeholder="Type your message here..."></textarea><br><br>

        <!-- Buttons -->
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
        <input type="reset" value="Reset">
    </form>

    <p><b>Note:</b> This form demonstrates input fields, text areas, and buttons used in HTML forms.</p>
</body>
</html>
